  "prompt": "What are the best places to eat vegetarian food in New Delhi?",
  "response": "New Delhi has a vibrant culinary scene, especially for vegetarian cuisine. Here are some of the best places to enjoy vegetarian food in the city:\n\n1. **Bukhara** - Located in ITC Maurya, this restaurant is famous for its North Indian cuisine, particularly its vegetarian kebabs and hearty meals.\n\n2. **Saravana Bhavan** - A well-known chain specializing in South Indian vegetarian dishes. Their dosas, idlis, and thalis are quite popular.\n\n3. **Haveli** - This restaurant offers a rustic dining experience with traditional Punjabi vegetarian dishes served in a charming ambiance.\n\n4. **Sagar Ratna** - Another popular chain, Sagar Ratna serves a variety of South Indian dishes, famous for their crispy dosas and flavorful sambars.\n\n5. **Cafe Lota** - Located in the National Crafts Museum, this cafe serves contemporary Indian dishes with a focus on regional vegetarian cuisine.\n\n6. **Komala Vilas** - A staple for South Indian food lovers, they are known for their authentic vegetarian meals and quick service.\n\n7. **Chacha's** - Offers a diverse vegetarian menu including North Indian and Chinese cuisine, with a cozy atmosphere.\n\n8. **Nukkad Cafe** - A casual dining place with an eclectic menu, it\u2019s a great spot for students and young adults looking for comfort food.\n\n9. **Pind Balluchi** - This restaurant brings the essence of Punjabi cuisine to life, offering a variety of vegetarian dishes in a vibrant setting.\n\n10. **The All American Diner** - A unique diner experience where you can find vegetarian burgers, salads, and other American-style dishes.\n\n11. **Khan Chacha** - Well-known for its delicious vegetarian wraps and rolls, it\u2019s a popular choice for a quick bite.\n\n12. **Veg Gulati** - A great place for North Indian vegetarian food, known for their variety of curries and tandoori dishes.\n\nThese places should give you a good taste of the diversity and richness of vegetarian food available in New Delhi!",
